{# ── DISCLOSURE BANNER · ABOVE THE FOLD (Sheet-7 honest-triage). Canonical .disclosure
     class (03-conversion.css) reused here. The inBrief above already states the NOT-Intuit
     boundary directly under the dark hero; this banner makes it unmissable a SECOND time
     and renders the explicit intent-split (talk-to-this-team vs. go-to-Intuit) as a
     checks-list with the Intuit support link. No new heading level — Sheet-7 requires the
     disclosure + intent redirect above the fold, the contract freezes the heading set. ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="qb-speak-disclosure">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="disclosure">
      <strong>TechBrot is an independent bookkeeping and Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not Intuit, not QuickBooks Customer Support, not QuickBooks Live, and not Intuit&rsquo;s expert or ProAdvisor referral line.</strong> Calling this number does not reach Intuit. &ldquo;Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor&rdquo; is a certification this firm holds from Intuit; it does not mean affiliation, endorsement, or sponsorship. This team cannot access your Intuit account, change your subscription, reset your login, or fix the QuickBooks software. For any Intuit account, billing, subscription, login, password, or product-bug matter, contact Intuit directly. What this team does is the accounting work inside your own books. This page is informational; it is not Intuit support.
    </div>
    <ul class="checks-list" id="qb-speak-boundaries">
      <li><strong>Talk to this team about your own books:</strong> QuickBooks setup, cleanup, migration, payroll, monthly bookkeeping, and advisory on your own QuickBooks file &mdash; the accounting work inside it.</li>
      <li><strong>Contact Intuit for the account itself:</strong> Intuit login, password, or two-factor; subscription, renewal, refund, or billing disputes; and QuickBooks software bugs, outages, or Intuit-side error codes. <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">Go to Intuit support &rarr;</a> &mdash; this team has no access to your Intuit account.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

